Studying Hebrew of the Hebrew Bible (Old Testament): analysing its grammar and syntax, translating its prose and simpler poetic texts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of this course is to equip the student with the basic tools necessary for reading the Hebrew Bible (Old Testament): to introduce the history of Hebrew language, its grammar and morphology, so the student will be able to read translate biblical texts with the help of dictionaries and course materials.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student will - know the main characteristics of the grammatical structure and morphology of the Old Testament Hebrew; - be able of analysing all the noun and verbal forms; - know the basic vocabulary of some hundreds of words; - be able of using dictionaries; - translate prose and simpler poetry of the Hebrew Bible (Old Testament) with the help of dictionaries.
